apps.graph
Class Visitor<T>

java.lang.Object
  apps.graph.Visitor<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of vertex objects stored in the graph to be visited.
Direct Known Subclasses:
ConnVisitor, TopVisitor
public class Visitor<T>
extends java.lang.Object

This class implements a visitor to used in directed graph traversals. It may be subclassed to implement application-specific actions when vertices are visited.

Author:
Sesh Venugopal

action

public void action(int vertex)
Performs an action at a given vertex, to be called when the vertex is visited. This implementation prints the vertex information, but does nothing else. Subclasses may override this method to add desired special features.

Parameters:
vertex - Vertex number of vertex for which action is to be performed.
